SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 41
BY SENATOR PRESSLY
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH. Recognizes March 17, 2026, as Profound Autism Day.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To recognize March 17, 2026, as Profound Autism Day.
3 WHEREAS, the definition of autism has evolved over the years, creating an
4 increasingly heterogeneous spectrum; and
5 WHEREAS, while the entire spectrum deserves recognition and support, profound
6 autism is a term intended to provide clarification about the autistic people who require 24/7
7 care from an adult caregiver throughout their lives; and
8 WHEREAS, people with profound autism can also have a severe intellectual
9 disability with minimal or no language; and
10 WHEREAS, these individuals are frequently excluded from research and support
11 programs because of their unique needs; and
12 WHEREAS, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention released their first
13 prevalence study on profound autism in April 2023; and
14 WHEREAS, the research concluded that the percentage of 8-year-old children with
15 profound autism among those with autism in the United States was 26.7%, meaning that one
16 in four children with autism have profound autism; and
17 WHEREAS, compared with children with nonprofound autism, children with
18 profound autism were more likely to be female, from racial and ethnic minority groups, of
