1 low socioeconomic status, born preterm or with low birth weight, have self-injurious
2 behaviors, seizure disorders, and lower adaptive scores; and
3 WHEREAS, people with profound autism and those who care for them live in our
4 midst, frequently in isolation, and need our inclusion and support; and
5 WHEREAS, specific consideration of the unique challenges facing individuals with
6 profound autism is critical.
7 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
8 does hereby recognize March 17, 2026, as Profound Autism Day.
9 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
10 Profound Autism Alliance.
